 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uranariusspiritarrow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ranarius Spiritarrow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 343<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/27/01 11:59:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Indies on Dragon Rotations</span><hr size=1> Well I didn't know if we could reply, or just vote when I first voted yes.<br>
<br>
This specific poll makes me sick.  Who here, on this board, or in the game, has the right to tell another player how to play this game?  It's just so obvious.  If you want to make 100% sure indies are not cheating the system, there are SO many other ways to do it.  But taking their rights away is not one of them.  <br>
<br>
When a guild signs up for a raid, you can almost always bet that they'll be taking at LEAST 12 of their own people.  That seems very reasonable to me.  <br>
<br>
So maybe if you REALLY REALLY care about this issue, just have indies get 12 sponsers to sign up under their name when they sign up, saying that they will be helping out on the raid.  Even doing this takes away some rights.  But if it has to happen to keep the people with all the power happy, then I guess it has to happen.  At least the average player will still get a chance to kill a dragon without having to have friends in high places.<br>
<br>
Example:<br>
1. Indy signs up for Trakanon.<br>
2. His name is added to the rotation list as pending.<br>
3. Leave his post there for people to &quot;sponser&quot; his raid until 12 are there.<br>
4. Remove the pending status from his name.<br>
5. Delete the post with the 12 sign ups.<br>
6. His turn comes up, and everyone has fun.<br>
<br>
By taking away indy sign ups, you are pretty much assuming guilty until proven innocent.  We all know who has abused the system in the past.  But don't make others pay for their mistakes. <p><a href=http://interealms.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=6277>Ranarius Spiritarrow</a><BR><a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/bsentinelsoftunare>Sentinels Of Tunare</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=visceratpersequor>Viscerat Persequor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/28/01 12:22:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Indies on Dragon Rotations</span><hr size=1> I have to agree, the thought of taking indies off of dragon rotations is sickening. As far as players rights are concerned, we all pay every month to play, and that ten bucks buys each player his or her rights to do as he or she wishes in eq, now, i'm not saying that they can do *anything* they want, but, none of us has the right to say that anyone else can't go wherever they want. Now, if we were roleplaying, i think that there would be a more interesting edge to it, say, (for example), that Evoluxa and SR both wanted to kill trak, on the same day, there's nothing to stop either raiding party from going after him, the only thing they have to fear is they're reputations being hurt. Furthermore, I'd like to see somebody, in particular, a group of mostly indies say &quot;We beat (fill in guild name here) to trak for the kill&quot;. I don't like the fact that guilds are the ruling class in eq. How many guild members here even remember the purpose for their guild, (or mission statement if you want to call it that), and those of you that do remember it, how many of you actually stick to that code, I know that i couldn't tell you my guilds purpose anymore, and i doubt that we even follow traditions anymore. I'm not trying to offend anyone, (mostly because i do recognize that guilds are the ruling class, and i don't want to be excluded from anything in the future for stating my opinion), but, brell is starting to feel like it's being carved up into bits of timeshare condos, &quot;you can have trak on the evenings of the the 2nd and 4th spawns of the month, and we'll take him on the first and third, and if there is a 5th spawn, it's FFA, sound good??&quot;, and frankly, i don't want to see a very fun game turned into something that feels like a corporation. Some of the guilds are beginning to remind me of verant, and we all know how evil verant can be, (j/k).<br>
OK, I'm done with my tangent now, goodnight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usstiyrr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sstiyrr</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 229<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/28/01 1:16:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Indies on Dragon Rotations</span><hr size=1> Ok, guys, lets take it straight.<br>
<br>
